<item>
            <title>[LU-20114] ldlm_reclaim_threshold underestimates per-lock memory cost</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20114</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ldlm_ratio2locknr()&lt;/tt&gt; estimates the memory cost per lock using only &lt;tt&gt;sizeof(struct ldlm_lock)&lt;/tt&gt;, but in reality, each lock is associated with multiple additional structures, making the effective cost about 1.6&#215; higher. As a result, &lt;tt&gt;ldlm_reclaim_threshold&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;ldlm_lock_limit&lt;/tt&gt; are too lenient, and reclaim is not triggered before reaching OOM.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
